            <h1>About Me</h1>
            <p>My name is Ethan Emmanuel Isakir, and I am a 10th-grade student at The Browning School in New York City. Growing up in Forest Hills, Queens has given me a strong appreciation for academics, teamwork, and competition.</p>
            
            <p>I am passionate about business and aspire to pursue a career in entrepreneurship or finance. Track & Field is a major part of my life — it has taught me discipline, resilience, and the drive to constantly improve.</p>
            
            <p>I compete in Track, Soccer, and Ping Pong, and I volunteer at MoMath. These experiences continue to shape me into a well-rounded leader and problem solver.</p>
